#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:2
msgid "prometheus-application-metrics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:4
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Yes. Istio ships with `configuration for Prometheus "
"<%7B%7B%3C%20github_file%20%3E%7D%7D/install/kubernetes/helm/istio/charts/prometheus/templates/configmap.yaml>`_"
" that enables collection of application metrics when mutual TLS is "
"enabled or disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:9
msgid ""
"The ``kubernetes-pods`` job collects application metrics from pods in "
"environments without mutual TLS. The ``kubernetes-pods-istio-secure`` job"
" collects metrics from application pods when mutual TLS is enabled for "
"Istio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:14
msgid ""
"Both jobs require that the following annotations are added to any "
"deployments from which application metric collection is desired:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:17
msgid "``prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:18
msgid "``prometheus.io/path: \"<metrics path>\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:19
msgid "``prometheus.io/port: \"<metrics port>\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:21
msgid "A few notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:23
msgid ""
"If the Prometheus pod started before the Istio Citadel pod could generate"
" the required certificates and distribute them to Prometheus, the "
"Prometheus pod will need to be restarted in order to collect from mutual "
"TLS-protected targets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/metrics-and-logs/prometheus-application-metrics.rst:27
msgid ""
"If your application exposes Prometheus metrics on a dedicated port, that "
"port should be added to the service and deployment specifications."
msgstr ""

